## 5. Page archetypes

### Landing (marketing)

**Density:** spacious. **Scan:** Z-pattern.

Sections (compose with Stack primitive):
1. **Header / nav** — sticky, transparent over hero, opaque on scroll.
2. **Hero** — Cover primitive, 60–80vh. Headline (≤ 60 chars), subhead (≤ 2 sentences), 1 primary CTA, 1 optional secondary, visual.
3. **Social proof** — logos (4–8, grayscale) OR stats OR a single anchor testimonial.
4. **Features** — Grid of 3–4 cells. Icon (32px) + 2-word title + 1-sentence description.
5. **How it works** — 3 steps, numbered.
6. **Testimonials** — 1–3 with photo, name, title, company.
7. **Pricing** (optional) — 2–3 tiers, recommended tier visually emphasized.
8. **FAQ** — 5–8 questions in `<details>` accordions.
9. **Final CTA** — repeats hero CTA with different framing.
10. **Footer** — 3–5 columns of links + copyright + social.

Pull copy and names from `[.mba-template/content/sample-content.json](mdc:.mba-template/content/sample-content.json)`. See `[.mba-template/patterns/landing-page-sections.md](mdc:.mba-template/patterns/landing-page-sections.md)`.

**The "landing" archetype above is the SaaS funnel.** It is the wrong skeleton for a brick-and-mortar shop, restaurant, salon, clinic, agency, or any real-world business that doesn't sell software subscriptions. For those, use the **local-business / retail** archetype below.

### Local-business / retail / hospitality

**Use when:** the brief is a pet shop, bakery, café, restaurant, salon, gym, yoga studio, dental clinic, real-estate agent, photographer, florist, boutique, pet groomer, daycare, or any other business with a physical location and/or a product catalog (not a SaaS subscription).

**Density:** spacious. **Mode:** light by default (warmth and trust matter more than monochrome restraint). **Scan:** F-pattern for product/service grids, Z-pattern for the hero. **Imagery:** real photographs are **mandatory** — see `[.mba-template/patterns/imagery-and-photography.md](mdc:.mba-template/patterns/imagery-and-photography.md)`.

Sections (compose with Stack primitive — pick the ones that fit; rarely need all):

1. **Header / nav** — sticky, opaque (not transparent over a photo hero — text becomes unreadable). Brand wordmark + 3–5 nav items + a single primary CTA matching the business ("Visit us", "Shop", "Book a table", "Book grooming").
2. **Hero** — Cover primitive, 60–80vh. **Real full-bleed photograph** of the product, the place, or the people/animals/food the business is about. Headline overlay (one-sentence promise: "Everything your dog needs, in one warm shop on Main Street."). 1 primary CTA appropriate to the business. Avoid generic "Start free" — this isn't an app.
3. **Featured products / categories OR services** — Grid of 4–8 cells, each with: real product photo (square or 4:5), name, price OR "From $X" OR a short description. For a pet shop: Food, Toys, Beds, Aquariums, Small Pets. For a salon: Cut, Color, Treatments. Image is the focus, text is secondary.
4. **About / our story** — Stack with one warm photo (interior, owner, team) + 2–3 short paragraphs. Authenticity matters more than wordcount. Mention founding year, location, what makes the place specific.
5. **Services** (optional) — separate from products. For pet shop: grooming, boarding, training. Each with photo, 1-sentence description, "Book" button, price range.
6. **Visit us / Find us** — Address, hours table, phone, embedded map (placeholder for Google Maps embed). For purely-online stores, swap for "Shipping & returns".
7. **Reviews / testimonials** — Real-sounding 1–3 reviews from actual local-customer-style names. Quote, name + city, optional rating (★★★★★). For pet shops: include the pet's name in the testimonial ("Bella has been coming here for 4 years — they always remember her").
8. **Gallery** (optional) — masonry or grid of 6–12 photos: store interior, products, happy customers/pets, staff at work. Real photos only. This is often the most-engaged section on a shop site.
9. **Newsletter / contact** — Single-field email signup OR contact form, framed warmly ("Get notified when new puppies arrive" / "Hear about our weekend pop-ups"). NOT "Subscribe to our newsletter."
10. **Footer** — Address + hours repeated (top reason people return to the site), social links (Instagram is critical for visual businesses), copyright, optional small links (Privacy, Returns).

**Sections to AVOID on a local-business site (these are SaaS-isms):** pricing tiers, free trial CTA, "How it works" three-step funnel, feature grid with stock icons, dashboard product UI screenshots, "1,247 users trust us" stat bars (use real reviews and a real Google rating instead).

**Reference systems:** Apple HIG for typography and restraint, Shopify storefront templates for product layout, Squarespace for warmth. Avoid Linear / Vercel Geist defaults — wrong register.

### Dashboard

**Density:** compact. **Scan:** F-pattern.

Layout (Sidebar primitive):
- **Header** (56–64px, sticky): brand, search, notifications, profile.
- **Sidebar** (240–280px, collapsible to 56px): nav grouped by section, active indicator, collapse toggle at bottom.
- **Main:**
  - Page header: H1 + breadcrumbs + actions (right) + filters (below).
  - Metrics row (Grid, 2–4 KPI cards with realistic numbers from sample-content).
  - Primary view: chart, table, or kanban.
  - Secondary view: activity feed or recent items.

**Required:** empty, loading (skeleton), error states for every data block. Realistic data — no `User 1`, `User 2`, `$1,000.00`. See `[.mba-template/patterns/dashboard-layouts.md](mdc:.mba-template/patterns/dashboard-layouts.md)`.

### Settings

**Density:** comfortable. **Scan:** F-pattern.

Layout: Sidebar (settings sub-nav, 200–240px) + main form. Or Stack (sections with anchor links) for shorter settings.

- Each section: H2 + 1-line description + form fields + section-scoped Save button OR sticky page Save bar at bottom.
- Use native `<form>` elements with `<fieldset>` for grouped fields.
- Destructive actions (delete account) live in their own section with red accent and confirmation dialog.

### Auth (login / signup / forgot password)

**Density:** comfortable. **Layout:** Cover primitive, max 400px content width.

- Brand at top.
- Heading (Welcome back / Create your account).
- 1–2 SSO buttons (Google, GitHub, Apple) — top, equally weighted.
- "or" divider.
- Email + password fields.
- Primary submit.
- Secondary link (Forgot? / Sign in instead).
- Optional: marketing visual on right half (desktop only, hide on mobile).

### Article / blog

**Density:** spacious. **Layout:** Single column, `max-width: 65ch` for prose, breakout for images/code/quotes.

- Header: title, author + date + reading time, optional cover image.
- Body: H2/H3 hierarchy, prose with `max-width: 65ch`, code blocks full-width, images with captions.
- Footer: author bio, related articles (Grid), comments (optional).

### Error (404, 500)

**Density:** spacious. **Layout:** Cover primitive.

- Large icon or illustration (don't generate — use icon library).
- Heading: "Page not found" / "Something went wrong".
- 1–2 sentences of helpful copy (not "Error 404").
- 2 actions: primary (Back to home), secondary (Search OR Contact support).
- Optional: top 3–5 popular page links.

### Search results

**Density:** comfortable. **Layout:** Sidebar (filters, 240px) + main (results stack).

- Search bar prominent at top with current query.
- Filters in sidebar: type, date, sort.
- Results: title (link, H3), 2-line snippet with query highlighted, metadata row (date, author, category).
- Pagination at bottom OR infinite scroll with "Load more" fallback.
- Empty state if no results: rephrase suggestion + recent searches.

### Profile

**Density:** comfortable. **Layout:** Cover-style header + Tabs below.

- Header: avatar (80–120px), name (H1), bio, stats cluster, action cluster (Follow / Message / Edit).
- Tabs: Posts / About / Activity.
- Content: Grid for visual posts, Stack for text posts.

### Checkout / payment

**Density:** comfortable. **Layout:** Sidebar (order summary, 360px, sticky) + main (form).

- Progress indicator at top (3–4 steps).
- Form sections in Stack: shipping → payment → review.
- Order summary on right, sticky on desktop, collapsible on mobile.
- Trust badges (lock icon + "Secure checkout") near payment fields.
- Primary CTA per step, never two competing CTAs.

