## 8. Self-check before returning

- [ ] **Vertical fit** — does the visual register match the business? (Pet shop ≠ fintech; restaurant ≠ CLI tool. See `[40-tone-and-vertical.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/40-tone-and-vertical.mdc)`.)
- [ ] **Imagery** — if the vertical is in the "imagery mandatory" list (retail, hospitality, wellness, agency, real estate, food, fashion, fitness, pets), is there at least one real photograph in the hero?
- [ ] **Skeleton fit** — for a brick-and-mortar / retail / service business, did you use the local-business archetype (with Visit Us, products, reviews) and NOT the SaaS landing skeleton (with pricing, trial CTA, feature funnel)?
- [ ] One primary action above the fold?
- [ ] If a secondary CTA exists in the hero, is it visually quieter by at least two signals (variant + size, or variant + no-icon)?
- [ ] Page committed to a single density (compact / comfortable / spacious)?
- [ ] Composed from primitives (Stack, Cluster, Grid, Sidebar, Switcher, Cover) — not one-off layouts?
- [ ] Scan pattern matches archetype (F or Z)?
- [ ] All data blocks have empty / loading / error states?
- [ ] Real content (names, copy, numbers) from `sample-content.json`?
- [ ] Mobile layout defined?
- [ ] Semantic landmarks (`<header>`, `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<aside>`, `<footer>`)?
- [ ] Heading hierarchy intact (one H1, then H2 → H3, no skips)?
- [ ] **All major sections share a single vertical padding value** (no mix of `--space-16`, `--space-20`, `--space-24` on the same page)?
- [ ] Zero raw `oklch(...)` / `#hex` / `rgb(...)` / `data:image/svg+xml,...` in component CSS?
